-- Peru Stocks: Credicorp, Intergroup, Rio Alto, Southern Copper
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-01-17T17:02:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/peru-stocks-credicorp-intergroup-rio-alto-southern-copper.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 11:45 a.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose, gaining 0.9 percent to
20,784.86. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  climbed 1.3 percent to
2,671.98.  Industrial and banking shares gained after U.S. stocks and
commodities advanced, said Estefany Castillo, an analyst at
Scotiabank Peru.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, rose 2.3 percent to $110.44.  Refineria la Pampilla SA 
(RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol YPF SA, climbed 2.2 percent to
92 centimos.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POM\C)  (POMALCC1 PE), a
sugar producer, gained 2 percent to 52 centimos.  Intergroup
Financial Services Corp. (IFS)  , the owner of Peru’s fourth-
largest bank, jumped 1.9 percent to $27.  Copper and gold miners rose after metals gained in New York
and  London .  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), the country’s biggest
producer of the metal, advanced 3.3 percent to $34.08.  Candente
Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration company, rose 2.9
percent to $1.05.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian
company with a mine in Peru, climbed 1.9 percent to $3.75.
 Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (SMCV)  (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., gained 1.8 percent to
$38.70.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
